    "what_description": "Ziziphora subcrispa is a perennial herbaceous plant belonging to the family Lamiaceae. Its botanical characteristics include a taproot system, a woody base, and a stem that is erect to ascending, hairy, and up to 10 cm tall. Leaves are opposite, ovate to lanceolate, 1-2 cm long, with a 2-3 mm long petiole, and have a hairy lower surface with a crenate or dentate margin. Flowers are small, in a terminal spike, and are a purple-brown color. Flowers are arranged in a cymose inflorescence and have a 5-merous calyx and a 4-lobed corolla.",
