    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Ziziphora subcrispa are digestive issues, diarrhea, indigestion and gastrointestinal disorders, which are often alleviated by its anti-inflammatory properties. Fever, inflammation and respiratory problems can be reduced due to its antipyretic and expectorant effects. Ziziphora subcrispa has also been used to treat skin irritation and insect bites, as well as nausea and vomiting, by its soothing and anti-inflammatory properties. Anxiety, headache, dyspepsia and abdominal pain can be alleviated by its sedative and analgesic properties, while cough and respiratory issues are often relieved by its expectorant effects. Stomachache and hiccups can be treated with Ziziphora subcrispa, utilizing its carminative and anti-spasmodic properties.",
