    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Ziziphora subcrispa are derived from its leaves and flowers, which are used for their carminative, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. Tea made from the leaves is used to alleviate digestive issues, such as bloating and gas, due to its volatile oil content, which includes alpha-pinene and borneol. A tincture of Ziziphora subcrispa is used to treat respiratory issues, including coughs and colds, due to its expectorant properties. An infusion of the leaves is used to reduce anxiety and promote relaxation, while its essential oil is used in aromatherapy to alleviate stress and promote sleep. A salve made from the leaves is used topically to treat skin irritations and wounds, due to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties.",
